TY  - JOUR
AU  - Amihud, Yakov
AU  - Goyenko, Ruslan
T1  - Mutual Fund's R2 as Predictor of Performance
PY  - 2013
Y1  - 2013/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhs182
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 26
IS  - 3
SP  - 667
EP  - 694
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We propose that fund performance can be predicted by its R2, obtained from a regression of its returns on a multifactor benchmark model. Lower R2 indicates greater selectivity, and it significantly predicts better performance. Stock funds sorted into lowest-quintile lagged R2 and highest-quintile lagged alpha produce significant annual alpha of 3.8%. Across funds, R2 is positively associated with fund size and negatively associated with its expenses and manager's tenure.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhs182
ER  - 



